_olex2_refinement_description     
;
1. Twinned data refinement
 Scales: 0.9991(2)
 0.0009(2)
2. Fixed Uiso
 At 1.2 times of:
  All C(H) groups, All N(H,H,H) groups
3. Restrained distances
 F1-B1 \\sim F1A-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F2-B1 \\sim F2A-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F3-B1 \\sim F3A-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F4-B1 \\sim F4A-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F1-F2 \\sim F1A-F2A
 with sigma of 0.04
 F1-F3 \\sim F1A-F3A
 with sigma of 0.04
 F1-F4 \\sim F1A-F4A
 with sigma of 0.04
 F2-F3 \\sim F2A-F3A
 with sigma of 0.04
 F2-F4 \\sim F2A-F4A
 with sigma of 0.04
 F3-F4 \\sim F3A-F4A
 with sigma of 0.04
4. Uiso/Uaniso restraints and constraints
All non-hydrogen atoms have similar U: within 2A with sigma of 0.04 and sigma
for terminal atoms of 0.08 within 2A
5. Rigid body (RIGU) restrains
 All non-hydrogen atoms
 with sigma for 1-2 distances of 0.004 and sigma for 1-3 distances of 0.004
6. Others
 Sof(F1A)=Sof(F2A)=Sof(F3A)=Sof(F4A)=1-FVAR(1)
 Sof(F1)=Sof(F2)=Sof(F3)=Sof(F4)=FVAR(1)
7.a Aromatic/amide H refined with riding coordinates:
 C2(H2), C3(H3), C4(H4), C5(H5), C6(H6)
7.b Idealised Me refined as rotating group:
 N1(H1A,H1B,H1C)
;

